Lots of rain- heat- and humidity this summer.  1/4" of rain yesterday morning.

~4 inches of rain in last week- including 1/2 inch last night.  Partly cloudy.
A very wet season- but almost no rain for the past week.  Very hot (~90 degrees)- but low humidity.  Lots of 'stuff' suspended in the water.
VERY hot last week (upper 90's)- with high humidity.  Almost no rain during that period- but ~3/4" Friday night (07/06/12)
Very hot this summer.  Very dry the past two weeks.  This is the worst I have ever seen the water.  It is really ugly.  Lots of floating algae and whatever else kinda of scum.
It has been extremely dry.  Very little rain.  I think it has been more than a month since the last 1/4 inch of rain in one event.  Water quality continues to be poor.  Very cloudy looking.
Just got the dock + boat in a few days ago (latest ever!).  Has been a cold + wet spring.  Lots of rain events lately- including 0.10" last night.

column2: Lots of rain this year- but none in the past five days.

column1: Has been clear and low-humidity the past several days- but humidity creeping up today.

column2: Water clarity very nice.  Not much rain the past two weeks- and incredibly cold (weekend just ended).  Nice today- but overcast at time of reading.

Has been a very wet spring.  Had 3" of rain on Tuesday (two days before this reading).

Lots of heavy rain events the past few weeks.
Appears that the lake just recently turned over.  It had been cloudy- but it is now clear.
Beautiful weekend: Warm- clear days; cool nights.
Plenty of rain this summer.  Last rain event was 08/04- and was a little over ?".
Lots of rain lately- including 1.75" last night.  Lots of crud washed into the lake from upstream- including a large (10' diameter) mass of pale yellow gelatinous-looking material.
